# Dev-mode env overrides — layered on top of ``.env.template`` and
# ``.env`` by ``machina dev`` (only). The ``machina start`` /
# ``machina daemon`` paths never load this file, so production-style
# runs keep the ``.env.template`` defaults (DATA_DIR=~/.machina).
#
# Loaded by ``cli.config.load_dev_overrides`` via ``os.environ.setdefault``
# so an explicit shell override (``DATA_DIR=/foo machina dev``) still
# wins. Committed to git as the canonical dev convention — every
# checkout's ``machina dev`` lands state in the same place.

# Per-checkout state under <repo>/.machina/ (resolved as a relative
# path under ``project_root()`` by ``core.paths.machina_root``).
# Multiple worktrees on the same machine each get their own clean
# DB / workspaces / temporal history; ``rm -rf`` of the worktree
# wipes the runtime state alongside the source.
DATA_DIR=.machina
